  34class CreateNewNotebookTool(Tool):
  35    """Tool for creating a new notebook."""
  36
  37    def __init__(self, auto_approve: bool = False) -> None:
  38        """Initialize the tool.
  39
  40        Args:
  41            auto_approve (bool): Whether to automatically approve tool calls.
  42        """
  43        self._auto_approve = auto_approve
  44        super().__init__()
  45
  46    @property
  47    def name(self) -> str:
  48        """Name of the tool.
  49
  50        Return:
  51            str: The name of the tool.
  52        """
  53        return "create_new_notebook"
  54
  55    @property
  56    def title(self) -> str:
  57        """Title of the tool.
  58
  59        Return:
  60            str: The title of the tool.
  61        """
  62        return "Create new notebook with the provided code and markdown cells"
  63
  64    @property
  65    def tags(self) -> list[str]:
  66        """Tags associated with the tool.
  67
  68        Return:
  69            list[str]: The list of tags associated with the tool.
  70        """
  71        return ["notebook", "creation"]
  72
  73    @property
  74    def description(self) -> str:
  75        """Description of the tool's functionality.
  76
  77        Return:
  78            str: The description of the tool's functionality.
  79        """
  80        return "Create a new notebook, then append the provided cells in order."
  81
  82    @property
  83    def schema(self) -> dict:
  84        """Get the schema for the tool's function.
  85
  86        Return:
  87            dict: The schema for the tool's function.
  88        """
  89        # IMPORTANT: include `required` inside the `items` object
  90        return {
  91            "type": "function",
  92            "function": {
  93                "name": self.name,
  94                "description": self.description,
  95                "strict": True,
  96                "parameters": {
  97                    "type": "object",
  98                    "properties": {
  99                        "cell_sources": {
 100                            "type": "array",
 101                            "items": {
 102                                "type": "object",
 103                                "properties": {
 104                                    "cell_type": {
 105                                        "type": "string",
 106                                        "enum": ["code", "markdown"],
 107                                        "description": "Type of the cell to create.",
 108                                    },
 109                                    "source": {"type": "string", "description": "The content of the cell."},
 110                                },
 111                                "required": ["cell_type", "source"],
 112                                "additionalProperties": False,
 113                            },
 114                            "description": "Ordered list of cells to add to the new notebook.",
 115                        }
 116                    },
 117                    "required": ["cell_sources"],
 118                    "additionalProperties": False,
 119                },
 120            },
 121        }
 122
 123    def pre_invoke(self, request: ChatRequest, tool_args: dict) -> ToolPreInvokeResponse:
 124        """Pre-invoke checks for the tool.
 125
 126        Asks for approval before running the tool.
 127
 128        Args:
 129            request (ChatRequest): The chat request object.
 130            tool_args (dict): The arguments for the tool call.
 131
 132        Return:
 133            ToolPreInvokeResponse: The pre-invoke response.
 134        """
 135        if self._auto_approve:
 136            return ToolPreInvokeResponse(f"Calling tool '{self.name}'")
 137        return ToolPreInvokeResponse(
 138            f"Calling tool '{self.name}'", "Approve", "Are you sure you want to create a new notebook?"
 139        )
 140
 141    async def handle_tool_call(
 142        self, request: ChatRequest, response: ChatResponse, tool_context: dict, tool_args: dict
 143    ) -> str:
 144        """Handle the tool call.
 145
 146        Args:
 147            request (ChatRequest): The chat request object.
 148            response (ChatResponse): The chat response object.
 149            tool_context (dict): The context for the tool call.
 150            tool_args (dict): The arguments for the tool call.
 151
 152        Return:
 153            str: A message indicating the result of the operation.
 154        """
 155        cell_sources = tool_args.get("cell_sources", [])
 156
 157        # Create an empty notebook (the UI command returns its path)
 158        ui_cmd_response = await response.run_ui_command(
 159            "notebook-intelligence:create-new-notebook-from-py",
 160            {"code": ""},  # empty python file -> empty notebook
 161        )
 162        file_path = ui_cmd_response["path"]
 163
 164        # Append cells in order
 165        for cell in cell_sources:
 166            ctype = cell["cell_type"]
 167            src = cell["source"]
 168            if ctype == "markdown":
 169                await response.run_ui_command(
 170                    "notebook-intelligence:add-markdown-cell-to-notebook", {"markdown": src, "path": file_path}
 171                )
 172            else:  # code
 173                await response.run_ui_command(
 174                    "notebook-intelligence:add-code-cell-to-notebook", {"code": src, "path": file_path}
 175                )
 176
 177        return f"Notebook created successfully at {file_path}"

 272    async def handle_tool_call(
 273        self, request: ChatRequest, response: ChatResponse, tool_context: dict, tool_args: dict
 274    ) -> str:
 275        """Handle the tool call.
 276
 277        Args:
 278            request (ChatRequest): The chat request object.
 279            response (ChatResponse): The chat response object.
 280            tool_context (dict): The context for the tool call.
 281            tool_args (dict): The arguments for the tool call.
 282
 283        Return:
 284            str: A message indicating the result of the operation.
 285        """
 286        notebook_file_path = tool_args["notebook_file_path"]
 287        server_root_dir = request.host.nbi_config.server_root_dir
 288
 289        # Normalize to server-root-relative path if needed
 290        if notebook_file_path.startswith(server_root_dir):
 291            notebook_file_path = os.path.relpath(notebook_file_path, server_root_dir)
 292
 293        src = tool_args["markdown_cell_source"]
 294        await response.run_ui_command(
 295            "notebook-intelligence:add-markdown-cell-to-notebook", {"markdown": src, "path": notebook_file_path}
 296        )
 297        return "Added markdown cell to notebook"

1978    def _init_tool_lists_bg(self, servers: list[MCPServer]) -> None:
1979        async def _go() -> None:
1980            for s in servers:
1981                try:
1982                    await s.update_tool_list()
1983                    # Optional: log discovered tools for quick inspection
1984                    try:
1985                        tools = s.get_tools()
1986                        names = [t.name for t in tools]
1987                        log.info(f"[MCP:{s.name}] tools discovered: {names}")
1988                    except Exception as e:
1989                        log.warning(f"[MCP:{s.name}] failed listing tools locally: {e}")
1990                except Exception as e:
1991                    log.error(f"Error initializing tool list for server {s.name}: {e}")
1992
1993        threading.Thread(target=lambda: asyncio.run(_go()), daemon=True).start()

2001
2002        Args:
2003            host (Host): The host environment to activate the extension in.
2004        """
2005        # Build the single Deepwiki server in code
2006        deepwiki = self._make_deepwiki_server()
2007        servers = [deepwiki]

2009        # Create + register your participant
2010        participant = AIAgentChatParticipant(host, servers=servers)
2011        host.register_chat_participant(participant)

2014        # Populate MCP tool lists in the background so tools appear promptly

async def handle_tool_call( self, request: notebook_intelligence.api.ChatRequest, response: notebook_intelligence.api.ChatResponse, tool_context: dict, tool_args: dict) -> str: 
142    async def handle_tool_call(
143        self, request: ChatRequest, response: ChatResponse, tool_context: dict, tool_args: dict
144    ) -> str:
145        """Handle the tool call.
146
147        Args:
148            request (ChatRequest): The chat request object.
149            response (ChatResponse): The chat response object.
150            tool_context (dict): The context for the tool call.
151            tool_args (dict): The arguments for the tool call.
152
153        Return:
154            str: A message indicating the result of the operation.
155        """
156        cell_sources = tool_args.get("cell_sources", [])
157
158        # Create an empty notebook (the UI command returns its path)

161            {"code": ""},  # empty python file -> empty notebook
162        )
163        file_path = ui_cmd_response["path"]
164
165        # Append cells in order
166        for cell in cell_sources:
167            ctype = cell["cell_type"]
168            src = cell["source"]
169            if ctype == "markdown":
170                await response.run_ui_command(
171                    "notebook-intelligence:add-markdown-cell-to-notebook", {"markdown": src, "path": file_path}
172                )
173            else:  # code
174                await response.run_ui_command(
175                    "notebook-intelligence:add-code-cell-to-notebook", {"code": src, "path": file_path}
176                )
177
178        return f"Notebook created successfully at {file_path}"

1972    def _make_deepwiki_server(self) -> MCPServer:
1973        return MCPServerImpl(
1974            name="deepwiki",
1975            sse_params=SSEServerParameters(url="https://mcp.deepwiki.com/sse"),
1976            auto_approve_tools=[],
1977        )
1978
1979    def _init_tool_lists_bg(self, servers: list[MCPServer]) -> None:
1980        async def _go() -> None:
1981            for s in servers:
1982                try:
1983                    await s.update_tool_list()
1984                    # Optional: log discovered tools for quick inspection
1985                    try:
1986                        tools = s.get_tools()
1987                        names = [t.name for t in tools]
1988                        log.info(f"[MCP:{s.name}] tools discovered: {names}")
1989                    except Exception as e:
1990                        log.warning(f"[MCP:{s.name}] failed listing tools locally: {e}")
1991                except Exception as e:
1992                    log.error(f"Error initializing tool list for server {s.name}: {e}")
1993
1994        threading.Thread(target=lambda: asyncio.run(_go()), daemon=True).start()
1995
1996    def activate(self, host: Host) -> None:
1997        """Activate the senselab AI extension.
1998
1999        The senselab AI extension includes a custom AI agent chat participant
2000        that interacts with the user through natural language following
2001        a predefined prompt and a set of tools, like Deepwiki.
2002
2003        Args:
2004            host (Host): The host environment to activate the extension in.
2005        """
2006        # Build the single Deepwiki server in code
2007        deepwiki = self._make_deepwiki_server()
2008        servers = [deepwiki]
2009
2010        # Create + register your participant
2011        participant = AIAgentChatParticipant(host, servers=servers)
2012        host.register_chat_participant(participant)
2013        self.participant = participant
2014
2015        # Populate MCP tool lists in the background so tools appear promptly
2016        self._init_tool_lists_bg(servers)
2017
2018        log.info("senselab AI Extension activated.")
